Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‎My father was a self-made factory owner. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.41,0:00:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He started a business working \Nwith rubber and plastics,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.41,0:00:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and we led a financially comfortable way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.29,0:00:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But in the middle of the 1970’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎things started going badly with his work. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.17,0:00:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎For this reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎he fell into a depression, \Nand he committed suicide. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.59,0:00:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎This was a great shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.85,0:00:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I went to the wall and wrote the words
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.27,0:00:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“He lives.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I didn’t want to believe that from that day on,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.27,0:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I wouldn’t see my father again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎At the age of about ten, I began to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‎strong antireligious tendencies. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.16,0:00:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And later, at the age of 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.37,0:01:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I also expressed them by participating
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.41,0:01:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in the most important incident
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.42,0:01:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎of the student movement \Nagainst the military junta
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.59,0:01:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that was prevailing in Greece \Nand ruling the country. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.76,0:01:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I became a member of the Communist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.60,0:01:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I went to Santorini and started a business. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.39,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I opened a bar. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.56,0:01:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Of course, all this included unsavory things
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.81,0:01:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‎like immorality, drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.98,0:01:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and plenty of alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.19,0:01:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎A few months later, \NI left to study in Germany. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.95,0:01:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It was the first time I met \Na brother engaging in street work. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.08,0:01:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎People would approach him,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.16,0:01:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and some would swear; \Nsome even spat at him. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.25,0:01:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It impressed me immensely
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.92,0:01:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‎how he stood calmly \Nand accepted this treatment. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.25,0:01:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎We had interesting conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.09,0:01:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,‎My studies ended, and I returned to Greece
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.92,0:01:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to take on the responsibility of the factory. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.01,0:01:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎When I finished my studies in Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:02:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I left with a sense of deep respect
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.60,0:02:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‎for Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.85,0:02:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The influence of my friends
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.94,0:02:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎led me to go into the military,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.94,0:02:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and there I saw a huge amount of corruption. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.45,0:02:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The hope I had that we humans
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.82,0:02:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎would be able to succeed \Nwithout external help 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.53,0:02:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—without God—\Nbegan to collapse, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.33,0:02:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and then the things I had heard
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‎from Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nsuddenly came to my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The same afternoon, \NI sought out a family friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.30,0:02:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the mother of a childhood friend, named Lily. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.26,0:02:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I said to her, “Please give me a Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and some Bible study publications\Nbecause I want to study them.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I read everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and anything that I didn’t understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I wrote down in a notebook. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I got to the point, in just a few days,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where I had written down 80 to 90 questions. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.28,0:02:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Harry impressed me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.45,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‎because every time I asked him a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‎he gave me the answer from the Bible. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎That convinced me that I’d found the truth. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So in that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.21,0:03:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I decided to leave the military \Nand to quit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.63,0:03:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‎A few months passed by,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where I was occupied mostly with the factory,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.63,0:03:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‎until I recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that for me to make progress in the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.56,0:03:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I had to sell my shares in the factory. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And on July 7, 1984, I was baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The authorities\N—the police, the mayor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the health inspectors—\Nbegan to demand money
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‎so that I could keep the bar open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.58,0:03:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I refused all the things they asked of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and so the war became harder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎until one night when I went \Nto open the door to enter my home;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.59,0:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I heard a tramping from behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I tried to turn and see,\Nand as I turned,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I was hit in the face. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‎During that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎when all of this was happening, \Nmy brother Dimitris arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.52,0:04:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‎As brothers, \Nwe never really had a relationship. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‎When he came to Santorini \Nand began to talk to me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and help me understand \Nwhat was happening to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.95,0:04:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I realized that this was a different Dimitris. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I said to him, “I want us \Nto start studying the Bible together.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I had the Bible with me \Nalmost everywhere I went
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎so that I could read it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.96,0:04:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I realized that Jehovah was helping me \Nto understand what I was living for. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.80,0:04:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He was helping me to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that I could have a real goal, a purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and a hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎On the day of my baptism,\NI felt that I was drawing closer to Jehovah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.06,0:04:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I felt like my smile went from ear to ear. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And now with Lydia,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:04:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I have the great joy of serving 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in the Romany territory. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎We enjoy very nice Bible studies. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.37,0:05:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It is truly something 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that shows you Jehovah’s love,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.75,0:05:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎interest, and affection
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—things that I had felt 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.59,0:05:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎many years ago \Nwhen I studied with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.09,0:05:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Today, my brother and I \Nlove each other very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It is a relationship characterized
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‎by brotherly love
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.64,0:05:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‎as it is expressed in the Bible. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.02,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‎We are very close to each other. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎This is really a change. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now we are truly brothers!
